{"word":"ποίμνη","slug":"ποίμνη","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ποίμνη</b></el> <el>(ποίμνη, ἡ,) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a flock</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; properly <i>of sheep</i> (<a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>ποιμήν</el>), <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; of a ram, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of persons, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}